<HL>
   Business Brief -- Bain &amp; Co.:
   Management Concern Forms
   Joint Venture With Soviets
</HL>
<DATE>
07/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A5
</SO>
<CO>
   FREST
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Bain &amp; Co., a Boston-based, international management
consulting firm, said it formed a joint venture in the Soviet
Union with the Soviet-based consulting firm Link Inc.
   As part of the joint venture, Bain will open an office in
Moscow to assist Bain's Western clients in evaluating and
pursuing business opportunities in the Soviet Union.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Bain will initially purchase a minority interest in the
venture, to be called BainLink, with an option to purchase a
majority of the venture's Western-owned shares at a later
date. Terms weren't disclosed.
   Bain said Link currently serves a number of Western
companies.
</TEXT>
